{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"a7ac81ca118e1dc58","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Do focused WEB research (WebSearch + WebFetch; cite URLs) for a self-improving local agent (\"Yogi\"). Do not answer from memory alone.\n\nCONTEXT: Yogi compounds in token-space. Its falsification bench currently shows a *directional* memory effect (Day-0 0.90 → Day-N 1.00) but cannot certify it (paired-bootstrap CI includes 0 at N=10). The Day-N path literally pre-loads the answer into memory, so it mostly tests retrieval, not genuine capability growth. I need to (a) make the bench measure MEANINGFUL compounding, and (b) wire a second compounding layer (verifier-fed SKILLS) beyond raw answer-memory.\n\nResearch and answer concretely:\n1. **Memorization vs. generalization in memory/agent benchmarks.** How do LoCoMo / LongMemEval / Letta skill-learning / Mem0 avoid measuring trivial answer-lookup? What makes a memory/skill benchmark test transfer (the lesson helps on *new* but related tasks) rather than recall of a stored answer? Concrete corpus-design rules (train/test separation by task vs by answer, held-out variants, paraphrase/transfer splits).\n2. **Sizing for a real compounding CI.** For a paired pass/fail bench, how many tasks + replications are needed for a paired-bootstrap (or McNemar) CI to exclude zero at a given true per-task effect size? Rules of thumb / power for proportions and paired binary outcomes.\n3. **Verifier-fed skill learning, concretely.** From Letta's skill-learning (and similar): what is the loop that turns a solved/failed trajectory into a reusable *skill note* that helps on FUTURE related tasks (not the same task)? How are skills retrieved and injected, and how does the verifier signal refine them? What made the +9%→+15.7% jump?\n4. **The other compounding layers' relative leverage** (skills vs routing/navigator vs distillation) for a 16 GB local build — which to wire next after memory.\n\nEND WITH a concrete RECOMMENDATION for Yogi's next step: how to (i) redesign the bench so it measures transfer not answer-lookup (a concrete corpus/split design + a sizing target), and (ii) wire verifier-fed skills as the second live compounding layer. Cite URLs throughout. Return findings only; do not edit files."},"uuid":"96fafca6-b342-462b-a16f-bf6ddd664fbb","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:13:14.730Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
