{"parentUuid":"aeff5bcd-e818-4aa3-82e1-72064bab03a8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"a7ac81ca118e1dc58","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_013eBKMMKSuRZw7z9nztuvua","content":"Launching skill: deep-research"}]},"uuid":"93a04070-2e91-4395-ab62-7699bbbc2d19","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:13:23.646Z","toolUseResult":{"success":true,"commandName":"deep-research"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"aeff5bcd-e818-4aa3-82e1-72064bab03a8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"93a04070-2e91-4395-ab62-7699bbbc2d19","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"a7ac81ca118e1dc58","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the \"deep-research\" workflow.\n\nDeep research harness — fan-out web searches, fetch sources, adversarially verify claims, synthesize a cited report.\n\nWhen the user wants a deep, multi-source, fact-checked research report on any topic. BEFORE invoking, check if the question is specific enough to research directly — if underspecified (e.g., \"what car to buy\" without budget/use-case/region), ask 2-3 clarifying questions to narrow scope. Then pass the refined question as args, weaving the answers in.\n\nPhases:\n- Scope: Decompose question (from args) into 5 search angles\n- Search: 5 parallel WebSearch agents, one per angle\n- Fetch: URL-dedup, fetch top 15 sources, extract falsifiable claims\n- Verify: 3-vote adversarial verification per claim (need 2/3 refutes to kill)\n- Synthesize: Merge semantic dupes, rank by confidence, cite sources\n\nInvoke: Workflow({ name: \"deep-research\", args: \"For a self-improving local agent (\\\"Yogi\\\") that compounds in token-space, research how to (a) make a falsification bench measure MEANINGFUL compounding (transfer, not trivial answer-lookup) and (b) wire verifier-fed SKILLS as a second compounding layer. Specifically: (1) Memorization vs generalization in memory/agent benchmarks — how LoCoMo, LongMemEval, Letta skill-learning, Mem0 avoid trivial answer-lookup; corpus-design rules for testing transfer (train/test separation by task vs answer, held-out variants, paraphrase/transfer splits). (2) Sizing a real compounding CI — how many tasks + replications for a paired-bootstrap or McNemar CI to exclude zero at a given true per-task effect size; power rules of thumb for paired binary outcomes. (3) Verifier-fed skill learning concretely — the loop from solved/failed trajectory to reusable skill note that helps FUTURE related tasks, how skills are retrieved/injected, how the verifier refines them, what drove Letta's +9%→+15.7% jump. (4) Relative leverage of compounding layers (skills vs routing/navigator vs distillation) for a 16GB local build — which to wire next after memory. End with a concrete RECOMMENDATION: (i) redesign the bench to measure transfer not answer-lookup (concrete corpus/split design + sizing target), (ii) wire verifier-fed skills as the second live compounding layer. Cite URLs throughout.\" })"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"6d281b2f-ea74-43c8-91de-21ed315faac3","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:13:23.564Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_013eBKMMKSuRZw7z9nztuvua","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
